Dialogue: 3,0:00:13.26,0:00:17.76,Callout,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(640,112)\fs21\c&H00988F8A&}// GARBAGE DATA FLOODING INTO THE FLIGHT COMPUTER; THE\NHORIZON...
Dialogue: 3,0:00:22.30,0:00:26.80,Callout,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(640,112)\fs21\c&H00988F8A&}// THE NOZZLES SLAM TO FULL DEFLECTION
Dialogue: 3,0:00:33.22,0:00:37.72,Callout,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(640,112)\fs21\c&H00988F8A&}// SIGNAL RED ENTERS FOR THE FIRST TIME
Dialogue: 10,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.45,Caption,,0,0,0,,But the flight computer didn't know\Nthat. It was still
Dialogue: 10,0:00:03.45,0:00:06.56,Caption,,0,0,0,,waiting for orientation data, and it\Ntook those error
Dialogue: 10,0:00:06.56,0:00:10.01,Caption,,0,0,0,,numbers and read them as if they were\Nreal —
Dialogue: 10,0:00:10.01,0:00:12.77,Caption,,0,0,0,,as if the rocket were violently off\Ncourse.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:13.11,0:00:16.73,Caption,,0,0,0,,So it did its job. It tried to correct.\NIt
Dialogue: 10,0:00:16.73,0:00:20.36,Caption,,0,0,0,,swung the engine nozzles hard over to\Nfix a problem
Dialogue: 10,0:00:20.36,0:00:21.81,Caption,,0,0,0,,that did not exist.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:22.15,0:00:26.22,Caption,,0,0,0,,The rocket obeyed. It pitched sharply,\Nat full power, into
Dialogue: 10,0:00:26.22,0:00:30.29,Caption,,0,0,0,,an angle it was never built to survive.\NThe aerodynamic
Dialogue: 10,0:00:30.29,0:00:32.73,Caption,,0,0,0,,forces hit it like a wall.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:33.07,0:00:36.88,Caption,,0,0,0,,The boosters began to tear away from the\Nmain stage.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:36.88,0:00:40.31,Caption,,0,0,0,,And the moment the rocket sensed itself\Nbreaking apart,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.31,0:00:44.12,Caption,,0,0,0,,its automatic self-destruct did the only\Nthing left to do
Dialogue: 10,0:00:44.12,0:00:47.94,Caption,,0,0,0,,— it detonated the vehicle, high over\Nthe launch site,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:47.94,0:00:50.61,Caption,,0,0,0,,before the wreckage could reach the\Nground.
